snippet: Mr. Williams imbued a lifetime of performances with a wild inventiveness and energy. The death was later ruled a suicide.
abstract: Robin Williams, comedian who evolved into surprisingly nuanced, Academy Award-winning actor, imbuing his performances with wild inventiveness and a kind of manic energy, dies at his home in Tiburon, Calif, at age 63; Marin County sheriff's office says death is suspected suicide due to asphyxia.

byline.contributor: Bruce Weber and Emma G. Fitzsimmons contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Mr. Williams imbued a lifetime of performances with a wild inventiveness and energy. The death was later ruled a suicide.

headline.main: Robin Williams, Oscar-Winning Comedian, Dies at 63
headline.print_headline: Robin Williams, Comic, Oscar-Winning Actor and TV Alien, Dies at 63
